---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Disclaimer"
  description="WorthCalc's calculators produce estimates for general information only. Not financial or investment advice."
  locale={locale}
  updated="2026-07-03"
>
  <p>
    <strong>WorthCalc's calculators are for general informational purposes
    only and do not constitute financial, investment, tax, legal, or other
    professional advice.</strong> Results are estimates only, not investment
    or financial advice — every calculator on this site simplifies a
    real-world decision into a set of formulas and the numbers you provide.
  </p>
  <h2>Estimates, not guarantees</h2>
  <p>
    Every calculator — including the installment true APR tool, subscription
    audit, Costco membership break-even, EV vs. gas TCO, rent vs. buy, commute
    cost comparison, latte factor, and cashback break-even — relies on
    simplified assumptions that are documented on each tool's page (for
    example, a fixed investment return rate or a flat annual price increase).
    Real-world outcomes depend on factors these calculators cannot know:
    future interest rates, market performance, inflation, your personal
    credit terms, promotional changes, and more. Small changes in assumptions
    can meaningfully change the result.
  </p>
  <h2>Not financial or investment advice</h2>
  <p>
    Nothing on this site should be interpreted as a recommendation to buy,
    sell, borrow, lease, subscribe to, or cancel any specific product,
    service, security, or financial instrument. Before making a significant
    financial decision — taking on debt, buying a home, purchasing a vehicle,
    or signing a membership contract — consider speaking with a licensed
    financial advisor, accountant, or other qualified professional who can
    review your complete financial situation.
  </p>
  <h2>No professional relationship</h2>
  <p>
    Using WorthCalc does not create an advisory, fiduciary, or professional
    relationship between you and the site operator. We are not a bank,
    lender, broker-dealer, registered investment advisor, or insurance
    provider.
  </p>
  <h2>Accuracy</h2>
  <p>
    We try to keep the underlying math correct and the default values
    reasonable, but accuracy is not guaranteed. Public figures referenced on
    tool pages (such as membership fee ranges) are approximate and may change
    over time; always verify current pricing and terms with the relevant
    provider before relying on a calculator's output for a real decision.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
